b'Experts Guide for the Media'
b'Sybil Derrible'
b'Associate professor of civil and materials engineering'
b'Biography'
b'Sybil Derrible is an associate professor of civil and materials\xc2\xa0engineering in the UIC College of Engineering and a research\xc2\xa0associate\xc2\xa0professor at the Institute for Environmental Science and Policy at UIC. His research focuses on the design of smart, sustainable and resilient urban infrastructure including transportation, water, sewer, electricity, gas and solid waste management.'
b''
b'Sybil Derrible.Photo: Roberta Dupuis-Devlin'
b'Derrible looks both at the demand for and the supply of services provided by urban infrastructure to develop resilient,\xc2\xa0efficient solutions for local agencies, city planners and utility companies. \xe2\x80\x9cWhether it is the water or wastewater system, the electricity grid, the buildings themselves, or the transportation system, all are part of a nexus of co-dependent and ubiquitous elements of infrastructure that is critical to our cities, acting as a significant generator of economic activity and social development,\xe2\x80\x9d says Derrible.'
